\n< Tim >Ah, h-how was it?

\n< Serena >There were a few books in my study that I had
never seen before.

\n< Serena >I would like to request a reservation,
but...

\n< Tim >I'll do it! I'll make a reservation! Which
one is it!? I'll keep it securely!

\n< Serena >N-No, I can't do that. Because of my unstable
situation right now, I don't know when
I'll be able to come and buy it.

\n< Serena >Well then, it would be a bother for the
store. Once my personal situation has
settled down, I will come again at that
time to make a reservation.
\n< Tim >I see...

\n< Tim >But, that's amazing. To have two or three
books that you've never seen before,
that means you have a study that rivals
our library, right?
\n< Serena >Yes... ah...
\n< Tim >？

\n< Serena >Oh no... Lord Tim, I have a secret request
about what just happened.
\n< Tim >That? Are you talking about the reservation?
\n< Serena >No, it's about the books in the library...

\n< Tim >......Ah, ah... That's right. Now that I think
about it, just how many expensive books
do you personally own...
\n< Serena >Lord Tim.

\n< Tim >Ah, s-sorry. But there's no one else
here...

\n< Serena >Even so, I apologize for involving you in my
slip of the tongue...

\n< Tim >Ahaha. It's okay. I'll sew my mouth shut. I
won't let those words slip out again.

\n< Serena >Thank you... There's a slightly special
circumstance...
\n< Tim >U-Understood... But, then, this, is it about that?
\n< Serena >？
\n< Tim >It's about the two of us, our secret, right?
\n< Serena >Hmm... Well, let's go with that.
\n< Tim >E-eh, ehe, ehehe.
\n< Serena >？
\n< Tim >S-Sorry. My face, it's smirking...
\n< Tim >Sorry, I'll go make some tea real quick!

\n< Serena >No, I can't stay for long. I have to go
home now...
\n< Serena >Hmm.

\n< Serena >Hello.

\n< Serena >I see... Well, I wasn't expecting much

\n< Serena >N-No, it's not like that.

\n< Serena >Ah, books are great. They nourish the

\n< Boy >Ehehe, you say nice things. My theory is that

\n< Serena >We seem to get along well. I'm Serena, an

\n< Tim >Oh, well, well. I am Tim.

\n< Tim >I'm also an adventurer, for the record. I'm
not very good at fighting, so I mostly
take on miscellaneous tasks like this...

\n< Serena >Is that so? Then we might have unknowingly
crossed paths at the guild.

\n< Tim >Well, I'm not sure about that. I'm not good
with the atmosphere there... so I try to
avoid going there as much as possible...

\n< Serena >Hehe, I feel the same way. The atmosphere
there is not good. First of all, the air
is bad. And there's no natural light
either.
\n< Tim >It feels like the adult world, doesn't it?

\n< Serena >I'm such a bad adult... Ah, I ended up
talking about something pointless.

\n< Serena >I apologize, but I must hurry. It was fun
talking, but I can't stay and chat too
long.

\n< Tim >Is that so? With a big belly, it must be,
um, really tough...
\n< Serena >Well... I guess so...

\n< Tim >Um, if it's okay with you, please come
again. Pregnant people can't move around
much, right? I think books or something
would definitely be helpful to you.
\n< Tim >Is that so? That's too bad.

\n< Tim >If it's okay with you, please come again.
The store manager won't be back for a
while, but we change the books every
day...

\n< Tim >If you love books, I think you'll enjoy
this store... um, I believe so...
\n< Serena >Yes. If I have time, I'll come by again.
\n< Serena >Well then, Lord Tim. I must take my leave.
\n< Tim >Phew... I got startled.

\n< Tim >She's such a cute girl. Her eyes are as red
as rubies.
\n< Tim >Serena-chan...
\n< Tim >I wonder if she'll come again...

\n< Serena >Well then, it's about time to return to the
brothel. I wonder what kind of new job
it will be...
